"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SELECT SUM(b.spent) \n     FROM budget b \n     JOIN event e ON b.link_to_event = e.event_id \n     WHERE YEAR(e.event_date) = 2019) \n    - \n    (SELECT SUM(b.spent) \n     FROM budget b \n     JOIN event e ON b.link_to_event = e.event_id \n     WHERE YEAR(e.event_date) = 2020) \n    AS difference_in_spent\n```\nThis SQL query calculates the difference in the total amount spent by the Student_Club between the years 2019 and 2020. It uses subqueries to sum the `spent` amounts from the `budget` table for each year, joining with the `event` table to filter by the `event_date` year. The difference is then computed by subtracting the total spent in 2020 from the total spent in 2019."